            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Trying to be everything to everyone. Positioning requires trade-offs. Brands that refuse to choose a single axis end up owning nothing in the customer's mind and get out-differentiated by focused competitors.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">How do I write a positioning statement?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
